(secondQuint)Efficacy of Tranexamic Acid In Reducing Blood Loss During Cesarean Section Because Of Placenta Previa.

 Tranexamic Acid used in the field of obstetrics to decrease blood loss during and after cesarean section .

 Tranexamic Acid is an antifibrinolytic agent which cause reversible and competitive blockade of the lysine binding sites in plasminogen molecules .

 It is a synthetic analog of amino acid lysine and its action is to reduce blood loss.

